    - 'Bramachari (梵志): A Brahmin in the first stage of the traditional Hindu life cycle.'
    - 'The Ten Stages (十地): The forty-first through fiftieth levels in the fifty-two-stage bodhisattva path.'
    - 'The three minds that cannot be grasped (三心不可得): Refers to the profound emptiness teaching of the Perfection of Wisdom doctrine—the past mind, present mind, and future mind cannot be apprehended as they are beyond conceptual designation.'
